##PROTECT THE RETROGRADE ANGELS: bypassing the Red Cross, they point-to-point delivery of supplies to hospitals around Wuhan

MICRO-SIGNAL YITIAOTV

Feature description, a short original video every day, every day to tell a moving story, every day selected human beauty, every day to live a better life with me.

Data Source: real-time tracking of new crown pneumonia in tencent

Recently, the hot search of the Wuhan Red Cross Society has steadily increased but not decreased,

From receiving $340 million in donations from the country, but allocating only $20 million;

Yesterday, the Red Cross Society of Hubei Province became the target of public criticism,

The allocation of goods and transparency have been greatly questioned,

And his response is flawed.

According to statistics, as of February 1,

The Wuhan Red Cross has received over $600 million in donations,

A Netizen said, "the problem I can't figure out every day these days is,

On the one hand, the shortage of materials in Wuhan is pressing; on the other hand, donations from all people are encouraging,

Where the hell is this stuff?"

"protect the retrograde angels" participants

Initiators Vermilion Bird, Liu Yufei, Wang Zhangwei (first row, left 1-3) 

And since the outbreak entered a state of emergency,

A number of voluntary non-profit organizations began to emerge,

They decided to organize a peer-to-peer public service initiative to directly link up hospitals,

One of them is "protect the retrograde angel. ".

On New Year's Eve, founder Suzaku and two friends

To form a grass-roots team,

Set Up "protect the retrograde angel" emergency public welfare action.

The three founders were entrepreneurs in small and medium sized companies,

With the addition of follow-up volunteers,

The core staff of 10 were divided into three groups,

To interface with the hospital, supplier selection, and follow-up.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Pressed for time and pressed for work, they quickly made a few decisions:

Nine hospitals around Wuhan were selected, focusing on four items such as face masks,

Communicate commercially, end the fight in 15 days.

"As the factory slowly recovers, our strength is no longer sufficient,

It's a fill-in."

As of January 29th, they are spreading through their friend circles,

A total of 298 donations were received, bringing the total to 370,000 yuan.

In the meantime, the hardest part isn't raising money,

It's about finding the right product quickly and accurately,

Run out of money and supplies quickly;

"The more money we have left in our accounts, the more nervous we are. "

And worst of all, people talk,

"normally we are the bosses of companies,

The front is fully engaged, the rear is reviled and questioned,

On the fourth day everyone's emotions exploded."

Finish the check before the Indonesian goods depart

When one of the initiators was contacted by a Rosefinch,

He had just secured a shipment from Indonesia, and he was exhausted,

He said, "it's probably hard for me to do it again,

If I have to do it a second time, I want to do it with these guys."

The Public Welfare project has just come to an end,

The three founders face an even bigger problem,

"because of the delay in resuming work,

Our own businesses are bleeding one hundred thousand to several million dollars a month,

As entrepreneurs, this crisis is forcing everyone to think,

How to face the future."

Self-described Suzaku editor Zhang Ruijia

Tian SA responded to the call to stay in Wuhan, in the home line to participate in collaboration

CAUSE: A big man in Wuhan cried on the phone

I was 85 years, my own business in Hangzhou, do a small company. When the epidemic began I was very concerned about the situation in Hubei, because I have a friend in Wuhan, a friend he is also one of our main members now, called Tian Sa. On the day of the 30th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China in 1930, I asked him on Wechat, "brother, what's going on over there? " He replied to many voices. He felt that Wuhan was an isolated island. He felt that he was trapped in an isolated island. Suddenly there were people outside who cared for him, it's like, all of a sudden, the big man is crying.

It just hit me. I thought maybe I could do something about it?

When SARS was still reading, is protected object, what can not do, today's Wuhan let a person heart-wrenching, all day there is a voice in the heart: We can do today?

I've actually been doing charity work for years, but it's all about giving money, and then it's over. On the evening of, Wang Zhangwei called me to say that he wanted to do something, he did 13 years of public welfare, but also have their own public welfare organizations, has been hands-on, their own fundraising, their own project, their own docking;

Wang Zhangwei pull up Hubei Entrepreneur Liu Yufei to participate together, that night the three of us set up a group of grass Taiwan began to do.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Two meals a day in front of the computer solution, every day unkempt in the study for 18 hours. "-SUZAKU

THREE NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATIONS SPONSORED BY SMALL AND MEDIUM-SIZED BUSINESS ENTREPRENEURS:

Communicate in a commercial way

Our small team had a background: We were all entrepreneurs in small and medium sized startups, and we were all business people. So slowly we found out the commonweal and usually do between the company.

With the upstream team docking hospital, then the next day the third day, we have a second team: docking suppliers to find goods, select goods.

In the early days of docking supplies, the members of Zhongyaqing, peach and I, I dealt with various suppliers more. Yaqing is a big seller of Taobao clothes and a good buyer. Peach has dealt with the medical industry before, and runs a community of mothers, there are high knowledge at home and abroad mother, these are our strengths. So the three of US formed this supplier docking team.

Because we all work together online, there are bound to be missed. Soon we set up an online graphite document. Wormwood was responsible for filling in all the key information, such as supplier information, such as follow-up after delivery, when to receive the goods, and how much the quantity was, whether there is a problem with the intermediate logistics and so on.

We have a total of more than 200 group Chat, many of the group content is very complex, this document can ensure that the information does not sink in the group, all people have all the information, not precipitation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Dong Qiguang participates in online collaboration at home

In fact, in this small organization,

Docking the hospital this group of people, in fact, docking is the customer, they want to understand customer needs;

Docking supply chain of people, equivalent to bd, that is, the buyer;

Then the end of the selection is required to follow up, this group is responsible for the landing of downstream materials follow-up;

We also know a Smart Lock Company boss Dong Qiguang, he is very familiar with logistics, responsible for coordination we can not solve the logistics problem;

There's a volunteer, who talks to our donors, in these 200-plus groups, to collect information that needs to be addressed, to reduce problems, to reduce misunderstandings;

Group of people to ask a variety of goods-related questions, very messy, I Yaqing and Dong Qiguang pull on the company's two designers, helped us design the material demand table, we probably want how many goods, what is the standard, how much price control.

Besides, I'm basically running the show.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Guardian of the Retrograde Angels Statement

Decision 1: Donate to the hospital point to point

We were always groping our way through the chaos, and the first day was the most chaotic.

The first day of work is divided into two parts: on the one hand to find suppliers to find masks, on the other hand to raise money. We three sponsors in the circle of friends to retweet the fund-raising message, but also with a Alipay Qr Code. Slowly, someone I knew came along.

We have a friend named Liu Yufei. He donated the most money among us. One person donated eighty thousand. He thought the fastest way was to donate money to the Red Cross. After the group talked about this plan, many people disagreed with it, you understand that, don't you? And the group began to disagree for the first time. Finally, he agreed with us and donated to the hospital point to point.

So by Wuhan Native Tian Sa, Entrepreneur Liu Yufei formed the first group, responsible for docking the upstream hospital. We need to make sure that all donations go directly to the hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the first day we focused on the hospitals in Wuhan, and on the second day we made a temporary change of direction: donating to the hospitals in the surrounding cities, because Wuhan already had the government and many caring organizations involved, and then we screened out nine of the surrounding hospitals, understand their needs, treat the number of people per day, according to the number of determine the amount of donations and supplies.

Most of these 9 hospitals are the ones where they have trouble finding us and where we have friends we know well. Because in fact, they were all hospitals in small towns and small towns, and people were also panicking. Some cases came in. First, the hospital did not know its specific needs at that time. Second, it did not know what would happen tomorrow. How long would this situation last? Everything's a mess.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
We must first bring the hospital responsible person into the group communication, and when the material arrives at the hospital, we all ask the hospital to issue a certificate with official seal, take photos and so on. It's actually a pretty brutal process, because the hospital is so busy, but to get all the details and the data, the hospital has to provide these certificates, and they have to fill in all kinds of information. But communicating with them is also a process of understanding the needs of users.

We also have several doctor friends in Wuhan who have been quarantined at home. So we pull in a supply review team, doctors, suppliers, we send it out to the group and ask if they're up to par. Is that all right? Does it work?

Decision two: We are a fill-in

Because of the small number of people and small energy, our initial orientation was to make up for the shortage within 15 days. The reason why we are so short of first-line supplies now is that the workers are not at work during the New Year. We are at a time when society has not fully reacted, as much as we can, we're still GONNA have to rely on the government.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Decision three: to spend money quickly, reserve materials;

The more money we have left in our accounts, the more nervous we get

We didn't realize on the first day that we were short of supplies, or even money, because we had only $50,000 on the first morning.

But with so many people joining in, money is no longer an issue. The second issue is demand: WE HAVE THE MONEY. What are we going to do with it?

Actually, when we raise $300,000, we don't want the money. At that time, many people gave us a silent alipay transfer money, there are two words wechat transfer, later I returned, because then the difficulty is not enough money, is money can not be spent. Supplies are hard to come by.

The more money we have in the account, the more nervous we become, the more we want to spend it all, not have it.

Decision 4: OFFER ONLY 4 categories and stay focused

We took stock of our capabilities and locked the supplies in four categories: masks, gloves, goggles, sanitizer, nothing else. Because we can't handle more than that. It's more focused.

During this period, many people also mentioned whether we should make protective clothing, or even whether we should dock with hospitals in Zhejiang, because later hospitals in Zhejiang also began to be in short supply. However, no matter what others say, we can not waver and keep our focus, otherwise we can not do well on both sides, it's the same as being a business.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Take photo before sending and after receiving the goods

The agreed supplier raised the price and could not get the goods out of the city,

The Split Second negotiations

We have different problems at every stage, and today is no exception.

It wasn't until an hour ago (on the afternoon of January 30th) that I felt much more relaxed, finishing off a shipment of Indonesian goods and putting an end to many problems.

We initially locked up a number of suppliers, need to communicate too many issues, qualification issues, volume issues, price issues, when delivery? What about logistics? About six or seven steps, all connected to pay for it. Today, a supplier has to pay the moment, a temporary double price, this time no one with you to sign a contract, you do not give it to others, the Split Second.

The purchase price of face masks has increased 2 times, 3 times, 5 times, 10 times as much as usual. The most exaggerated is the protective clothing, the first day of docking protective clothing suppliers, the normal market price of a set of 40,50, the result of a supplier to us 470. Finally, they said they'd give you $400 to watch you do charity work.

The first time we placed an order, we had no experience. The friend who was looking for goods found a supplier. When we hesitated whether the price was too high, the goods disappeared in a flash. The friend who was looking for goods was also very upset. The goods that had finally been found were gone again, then we got more experience, and we made a lot of quick, accurate decisions.

Later, I met a supplier in Jiangsu. The money had already been paid. When we delivered the goods, we were told that Jiangsu had closed the city. The goods were in a town under Jiangsu. We had a pro bono driver to pick up our load, and the local lockup was at 2:00 p.m. , but the factory wasn't finished until 2:00, and they had to do a decontamination process, so the load never left. Some governments allow the passage of donated goods, others do not, and some procedures are so complicated that they require government certification.

And I heard that other organizations paid for the goods on the road was requisitioned by the official, reasonable distribution, will eventually be sent to the major hospitals, but will be hit.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
One of the project sponsors, the orator Suzaku

Mission Accomplished. There's nothing more we can do

We were supposed to end the fight in 15 days, but it was basically over in five days, and now it's just over.

There's still a wave of $50,000 South Korean suppliers out there. Just received the goods from Indonesia today. Our overseas goods are all Chinese who have friends in the area and can be found in the local customs clearance company and issued relevant certificates.

Compared with other non-governmental public welfare organizations, we have advantages. We rely on the Public Welfare Organization of one of the sponsors, Wang Zhangwei. Therefore, we have all the qualifications, and the financial process is highly compliant. Indonesia has communicated with China Southern Airlines with our letter, can Open the green channel, goods can also be relatively fast smooth customs clearance landing.

Goods a moment not forever, our hearts are hanging, for fear of what problems in logistics.

With the recovery of the factories and the intervention of the government, our strength is not enough, we can only fill in the gaps, the rest of the work left to finish, make sure that the goods in the back are connected, and give an account to all the people in the group who donated money.

The hospital as a whole will certainly not because of our little efforts to alleviate all the lack of supplies is always, will always be short. Initially all eyes were on Wuhan, and the next day it dawned on me that Huanggang, Xiaogan, and Hangzhou and Wenzhou, all around us, were on the rise, but there was nothing more we could do.

In fact, I have been doing public welfare for many years, but it is limited to giving money, every time there is a major event or a friend in need, I donate money, donate my good heart to be satisfied, I do not ask where the money is spent.

This personally involved in, time is tight, the task is heavy, and in such a context to do public welfare, completely off a layer of skin. Emotions are there all the time, all the processes, all the details that can create them.

People talk. These days, in large groups, there are those who question the transparency of the data, those who are obstreperous, those who are one-track-minded, and those who criticize our management style. After speaking in groups, I still need to add your private message saying, "we were in a slightly better state on the second and third day of the eighth lunar month the other day, we say we're sorry, we didn't do it right, we could have done it better. The attitude is "admit your mistake and we'll try. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Until yesterday, our emotions exploded because we spent the most money, did the most work, and suffered the most. The administrator is too angry to kick a person, the money donated to her back, but to what extent? After the money back to her to add her back, explain clearly to get her forgiveness, because she donated money is also good, do not want to damage the reputation of the organization.

We this few people, everybody is to do business, who does not have a few cents temper? Originally in their own companies are the boss, today some people say that you do not manage well, the process is not right, not transparent, really angry do not know where to cast, too depressed.

Starting the next day, not only did we have an online comeback meeting every night, but I also had all the participants keep a diary in a graphite document. Last night I wrote this:

I don't think I can do this again, and if I have to do it again, I want to do it with these people.

I don't want this to happen again.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wang Zhangwei participates in online collaboration at home

Wang Zhangwei, who has been doing public welfare for 13 years, gave us a speech last night. He said, "although I have experienced the inner pain of being misunderstood, blamed and reviled for a long time, I thought I would be immune, but I still feel bad when I encounter it again. "

The last five days and four nights we've been doing this, none of us have slept very well. We call Ya Qing a girl is responsible for looking for suppliers, night dream are masks. Figured if I didn't find a supply of masks the next day, it was all for nothing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Meanwhile, peaches and her husband celebrate their 10th anniversary

"The 10th anniversary of a photo shoot without washing your hair or changing your clothes. "

Among our participants, there were men whose husbands had just had surgery, children who were sick, and people who had cancer that hadn't healed. The power of women is too great. There are several mothers who need to take care of their children. The line is busy saying "wait a minute, I'll make a dish for the children" . Yesterday was the tenth anniversary of Peach's wedding. Sometimes the family couldn't understand, why don't you take care of the people in front of you and worry about the people so far away? This is the worst kind.

All in all, what I'm trying to say is, I know that there are six or seven organizations like us, that do good and need to be seen, because it's not just doctors and nurses on the front lines, there are so many willing to roll up their sleeves around an angel in White.

It's enough to be understood, to be seen, not to be feared.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After rescuing others, it's time to worry about your own business

The last detail, just after the donation, is that we need to start worrying about our companies, and we need to prepare for a loss in the first quarter of 2020, a one hundred thousand to a few million dollars a month, this is a new challenge for our team.

Difficulties arising from the sales approach: The offline physical store sales-based business, all closed and stagnant, first quarter cash income is expected to be less than 10% of 2019;

Difficulties from operating categories: People are isolated at home, in addition to necessities and health products, affecting a large number of industries, and in the first half of the line sales place lack of passenger flow will be set in stone;

From the difficulties of upstream customers: e-commerce as the main business of warehousing distribution supply chain companies upstream customers can not start, and the cost of a large number of vacant warehouses can not be absorbed, the current situation is also a great blow to their own companies, can Not resume work can not operate, transport plate costs, storage plate costs, roughly estimated monthly loss of more than a million, do not dare to think down..

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Source: Lin Chen Hearing

Offline channels will be more active in a variety of ways to go online, such as live broadcast;
Health concerns are at an all-time high, and companies are changing their services and products to varying degrees.
This outbreak is forcing everyone to think about the future.
